---
import Base from '~/layouts/Base.astro';

const updated = '2026-04-22';
---

<Base title="Privacy policy — hookd" description="What hookd collects, why, and how to remove it.">
  <main id="main" class="w-full px-6 md:px-12 lg:px-16 py-section">
    <article class="max-w-prose mx-auto space-y-6 text-ink">
      <header class="space-y-2">
        <p class="font-mono text-sm text-ink-muted tracking-wide">hookd · from OpsKern</p>
        <h1 class="font-display font-bold text-4xl tracking-tight">Privacy policy</h1>
        <p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-ink-subtle">
          Last updated {updated}
        </p>
      </header>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="font-display text-2xl">What this page covers</h2>
        <p class="text-ink-muted">
          This policy covers <strong class="text-ink">opskernel.io</strong> — the hookd marketing site.
          It does <em>not</em> cover the hookd software you run on your machine. The software is local-first
          by design: your prompts and audit logs live on your device or on a server you control, and we
          never see them.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="font-display text-2xl">What we collect here</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-2 list-disc list-inside text-ink-muted">
          <li>
            <strong class="text-ink">Waitlist email</strong> — if you fill in the waitlist form, we store
            your email address in Buttondown so we can tell you when hookd is ready. Unsubscribe from
            any email.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong class="text-ink">Anonymous page views</strong> — we use Fathom, which is cookieless
            and does not build a profile of you.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong class="text-ink">Server logs</strong> — Cloudflare keeps short-lived edge logs of
            requests for abuse prevention.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="font-display text-2xl">What the software collects</h2>
        <p class="text-ink-muted">
          Nothing that leaves your machine. The classifier, policy rules, and hash-chained audit log
          run locally. If you deploy the Team Server, logs live on the server you chose. hookd does
          not send telemetry home.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="font-display text-2xl">How to remove your data</h2>
        <p class="text-ink-muted">
          Email <a class="text-accent underline" href="mailto:privacy@opskernel.io"
            >privacy@opskernel.io</a
          >. We will confirm identity and delete within 30 days.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="font-display text-2xl">Contact</h2>
        <p class="text-ink-muted">
          hookd is operated by Will Smith (pending LLC formation) —
          <a class="text-accent underline" href="mailto:hello@opskernel.io">hello@opskernel.io</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <p class="font-mono text-xs text-ink-subtle tracking-wide pt-6">
        <a href="/" class="hover:text-accent">← hookd home</a>
      </p>
    </article>
  </main>
</Base>
